Contents of /etc/sysconfig
==========================

Michal Svec <msvec@suse.cz>
If you have any updates, fixes or suggestions please send them to me.

Network configuration (network/):
---------------------------------
config		Global network settings
dhcp		DHCP client additional parameters
isdn		Global ISDN settings
routes		Static routes
wireless	Wireless devices settings
ifcfg-*		Network devices
ifroute-*	Static routes for a particular interface
providers/	Locally defined providers
scripts/	Network configuration helper scripts
if-up.d/	Directory with scripts to be executed on network start
if-down.d/	As above, but with network stop

See the "Network" file for a detailed description of the network
sysconfig configuration.

Configuration files:
--------------------
3ddiag		3D acceleration settings
SuSEfirewall2	SuSE firewall settings
amavis		Mail antivirus scanner settings
apache		Settings for apache(8) web server
argoups
argus
atftpd
autofs		Settings for autofs(8) (use nis, options)
autoinstall	Autoinstallation stuff (profiles location)
backup		System backup settings (backup dir)
baycomepp
boot		Boot process settings (confirmation, flow control)
bootloader	Boot loader settings (boot loader type)
clock		Clock settings (timezone)
console		Console settings (font, encoding)
cron		Settings for cron(8) scripts (files to delete)
devfs
dhcpd		Settings for dhcpd(8) (interface, user)
dhcrelay
displaymanager	Display manager configuration (xdm|kdm|gdm)
distccd
dracd
dvb
hardware	Hardware settings (dma devices)
hotplug		Hot pluggable devices settings (pci, usb)
intermezzo
ipvsadm
irda		IrDA settings (default port)
ispell		Settings for ispell(1) (dictionary)
java		Java settings (symlink, threads type)
joystick	Joystick settings (port, modules)
kernel		Kernel and initrd settings (initrd modules)
keyboard	Keyboard settings (console map, speed)
language	Language settings (default language)
lisa
locate		Settings for locate (updatedb(1) params)
lshd
lvm		LVM settings (activate on boot)
mail		General mail settings for all MTA (From header)
mouse		Mouse settings (device, console type)
news		News settings (organization, nntp server)
nfs		NFS settings (nfsd protocol number)
noflushd
ntopd
onlineupdate	YaST2 online update settings (reg code)
openldap
otrs
pcmcia		PCMCIA settings (system type)
pcnfsd
plip
postfix		Parameters for postfix(1)
postgresql
powermanagement
printer		Printer settings (default printer)
proxy		Proxy settings (www and ftp proxy)
radvd		Parameters for radvd(8)
rplay
saftemon
secumod
security	Security settings
sendmail	Parameters for sendmail(8)
smartups
snort
sound		Sound settings (load sequencer)
spamd
ssh		Parameters for sshd(8)
suseconfig	SuSEconfig settings (mailto, logs, groff settings)
susehelp
sysctl		System control settings (ip forward, sysrq)
syslog		Parameters for syslogd(8)
tetex		Settings for TeX
tux
windowmanager	Window manager settings (wm scheme, default wm)
xdmsc
xntp		Parameters for xntpd(8)
ypbind		Parameters for ypbind(8)
ypserv		Parameters for ypserv(8) and rpc.yppasswdd(8)
zope		Parameters for zope (http port)
